  <static seed="1478" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalLiteralEquations/LiteralEquation280.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve this equation for <m>C</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{7C} = \frac{1}{t} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>C = \frac{t}{7}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To solve this equation, we multiple both sides with the common denominator <m>{7Ct}</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{1}{7C} \amp = \frac{1}{t}  \\
   \frac{1}{7C} \cdot 7Ct \amp = \frac{1}{t} \cdot 7Ct \\
   t \amp = 7C \\
   \frac{t}{7} \amp = \frac{7C}{7} \\
   \frac{t}{7} \amp = C \\
   C \amp = \frac{t}{7}
\end{aligned}
}</m></p>
</solution>
